      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. it's just hard because it’s so subtle. like, i was looking at the latest amendment draft today and the specific phrasing in section 4.2—the part about the regional dispute resolution protocol—is word-for-word what i proposed during the closed-door sessions. but my name isn't on any of the metadata or the signatory lists. it's like they've systematically scrubbed my fingerprints off the actual logic of the treaty. do you think they're doing this to keep me in this \"analyst\" role, or is it something more intentional to keep my influence off the record?",
